Clarence Thomas rose from an impoverished childhood to a seat on the
Supreme Court.  The greatest influence in his life was his grandfather
who taught him values that anchored his conservatism. He earned a Yale
law degree. He held a variety of lesser posts before reaching the
Supreme Court.</SUM>
